revision.text: Possibly: Memoirs of two young gentlemen. Exhibiting the most striking instances of the seduction and snares to which young people are liable ... Interspersed with awful warnings...By N. (Probably James Nassau: the two young gentlement are probaly James Nassau and Josiah Tomkins - see later editions). (Edinburgh : Printed by J. Reid ; And sold at his printing-office, and by all the Booksellers in town and country, 1768). http://www.worldcat.org/oclc/722510160
